    passage:`<p style="font-weight:700;font-size:15.5px;margin-bottom:10px">Online Article: The Rise of Sustainable Packaging</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">As environmental concerns continue to shape consumer behavior, more companies are turning to sustainable packaging solutions. A recent industry study found that 73 percent of global consumers say they would definitely or probably change their consumption habits to reduce environmental impact.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">In response, many leading brands have committed to eliminating single-use plastics from their packaging by 2025. Several major retailers have already transitioned to biodegradable materials for their product packaging, seeing positive customer responses as a result.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">However, the transition is not without challenges. Sustainable materials can cost up to forty percent more than conventional packaging, and supply chains for eco-friendly materials are still developing. Small and medium-sized businesses, in particular, face greater financial pressure in making the switch.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2">Despite these challenges, industry analysts predict that sustainable packaging will become the standard within the next decade, driven by both regulatory pressure and growing consumer demand.</p>`,
