    passage:`<p style="font-weight:700;font-size:15.5px;margin-bottom:10px">Travel Advisory: Visiting the Sonora Region</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">The Sonora Tourism Board is pleased to announce that the Sonora Valley Heritage Trail, a 45-kilometer hiking route connecting six historic villages, has reopened following extensive trail restoration work. The trail had been closed for eight months due to damage caused by severe flooding last winter.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">Hikers are advised that sections of the northern portion of the trail remain challenging due to ongoing erosion repair work. Visitors are strongly encouraged to carry detailed maps and notify local ranger stations of their planned route before setting out.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2;margin-bottom:9px">The Sonora Valley Visitor Center, located at the trailhead in the village of Maravilla, offers guided hikes every Saturday and Sunday morning at 8:00 A.M. from May through October. Advance booking is required and can be completed online at sonora-tourism.org.</p>
<p style="font-size:15px;line-height:2">For trail conditions and updates, hikers are encouraged to check the tourism board's website or contact local ranger stations directly.</p>`,
